              what would be the probability that the particle would be found in the region <m>x \lt 5</m>?
              Explain briefly how you calculated this from the Excel worksheet.
              <em>Hint:</em> Remember that for a continuous wavefunction <m>\psi(x)</m>,
              the probability of finding the particle in a particular region is <m>\int_{x_1}^{x_2} P(x)\, dx = \int |\psi (x)|^2\, dx</m>.
              However, we don't actually have a wave function to integrate;
              we have a numerical solution instead.
              But we can do a <em>Riemann Sum</em>
              and add up the contributions:
              <m>\sum_i P(x_i)\, \Delta x = \sum |\psi(x_i)|^2\, \Delta x</m>.
              You'll have to determine what
              <m>\Delta x</m> is in this Excel worksheet.
            </p>
          </li>
